15/02/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The trial of a former Croatian military police member, Kreso Lucic, who is charged with war crimes against Bosniak civilians, began in the BiH Court on Wednesday (February 14th). Lucic, the ex-commander of the Croatian Defence Council's military police in Kresevo, is charged with the 1992-1993 imprisonment and torture of Bosniak civilians in Kresevo, Kiseljak, Busovac and Vitez. The first witnesses are expected testify next week. (RTRS, Srna - 14/02/07)
